			<name>
				<baseName xml:lang="en">Contaminated soil</baseName>
				<baseName xml:lang="zh">受到污染的土壤</baseName>
			</name>
			<common:synonyms xml:lang="en">Soil pollution; Soil contamination</common:synonyms>
			<common:synonyms xml:lang="zh">Soil pollution; Soil contamination</common:synonyms>
			<classificationInformation>
				<common:classification name="ILCD 1.1" classes="../ILCDClassification.xml">
					<common:class level="0">Materials production</common:class>
					<common:class level="1">Other materials</common:class>
				</common:classification>
			</classificationInformation>
			<common:generalComment xml:lang="en">Contaminated soil refers to the presence of toxic chemicals in soil that exceed naturally occurring levels and pose risks to human health and the environment. These contaminants can leach into ground or surface waters, be taken up by plants and animals, contaminate drinking water supplies, or volatilize and affect indoor air quality. Soil contamination can result from pesticides, petroleum products, asbestos, lead, and other hazardous substances. It can be localized or widespread, and is a significant global concern, particularly severe in regions like Europe, Eurasia, Asia, and North Africa. The EPA aims to prevent adverse effects by protecting soil integrity, while the FAO reports that one-third of the world's soil is already severely or moderately degraded.</common:generalComment>
			<common:generalComment xml:lang="zh">土壤污染是指土壤中存在的有毒化学物质超过了天然存在的水平，对人类健康和环境造成危害。这些污染物会渗入地下水或地表水，被动植物吸收，污染饮用水供应，或挥发影响室内空气质量。土壤污染可能由杀虫剂、石油产品、石棉、铅和其他有害物质造成。土壤污染可以是局部的，也可以是大范围的，是一个全球关注的重大问题，在欧洲、欧亚大陆、亚洲和北非等地区尤为严重。美国环保局的目标是通过保护土壤完整性来防止不利影响，而联合国粮农组织报告称，全球三分之一的土壤已经严重或中度退化。</common:generalComment>
